research_municipality_step.notes: Jersey City operates under a mayor-council government system. James Solomon was elected Mayor in December 2025 and assumed office in 2026. The City Council consists of nine members: six ward council members and three at-large council members. The provided search results from January 2026 confirm Denise Ridley (Ward A), Joel Brooks (Ward B), Tom Zuppa (Ward C), and Frank Gilmore (Ward F) as members of the incoming council. The remaining five individuals (Ephros, Little, Griffin, Singh, and Lavaro) are also listed as 'council members elect' for the new administration. However, their specific ward assignments (Ward D, Ward E) or at-large status are not explicitly detailed in the provided information, nor are their full names available in the snippets.
